					</group_input>
				</stacked_container>
				<text_box font_size="11pt" appearance="transparent" x="16.5846" y="88.9534" width="361.281" height="142.8">The default settings for the tool are for parameterised for England population (aged 18+). To use this tool for a smaller population, it will be necessary to manually overwrite the following values/estimates (ideally, use January 2025)

* enter 0 if not known, the model will find dynamic equilibrium.

NOTE: the Baseline runs in the charts will not update, so should not be used to compare against a new run.</text_box>
				<stacked_container x="12.8771" y="241.753" width="368.696" height="332.462">
					<group_input font_size="11pt" header_font_size="11pt" width="368.696" height="332.462" title="Initial Values">
						<numeric_input title="Population in 2025 (aged 18+)">
							<format precision="1" scale_by="1" delimit_000s="true"/>
							<entity name="calcs.init_pop_18_2025"/>
							<reset_to after="never">0</reset_to>
						</numeric_input>
						<numeric_input title="Number waiting for first OPA">
							<format precision="1" scale_by="1" delimit_000s="true"/>
							<entity name="calcs.init_wait_opa"/>
							<reset_to after="never">0</reset_to>
						</numeric_input>
						<numeric_input title="Number with DTA">
							<format precision="1" scale_by="1" delimit_000s="true"/>
							<entity name="calcs.init_wait_admit"/>
							<reset_to after="never">0</reset_to>
						</numeric_input>
						<numeric_input title="Number waiting for pre-op assessment *">
							<format precision="1" scale_by="1" delimit_000s="true"/>
							<entity name="calcs.init_wait_poa"/>
							<reset_to after="never">0</reset_to>
						</numeric_input>
						<numeric_input title="Number waiting for medical optimisation *">
							<format precision="1" scale_by="1" delimit_000s="true"/>
							<entity name="calcs.init_wait_opt"/>
							<reset_to after="never">0</reset_to>
						</numeric_input>
						<numeric_input title="Number being treated/recovering *">
							<format precision="1" scale_by="1" delimit_000s="true"/>
							<entity name="calcs.init_treat"/>
							<reset_to after="never">0</reset_to>
						</numeric_input>
						<numeric_input title="Number in hospital with delayed discharge *">
							<format precision="1" scale_by="1" delimit_000s="true"/>
							<entity name="calcs.init_delay"/>
							<reset_to after="never">0</reset_to>
						</numeric_input>
						<numeric_input title="Capacity: O&amp;T 1st OPA per week">
							<format precision="1" scale_by="1" delimit_000s="true"/>
							<entity name='calcs."new_o&amp;t_opa_per_week"'/>
							<reset_to after="never">0</reset_to>
						</numeric_input>
						<numeric_input title="Capacity: O&amp;T planned 4-hr theatre sessions per week">
							<format precision="1" scale_by="1" delimit_000s="true"/>
							<entity name='calcs."new_4-hr_sess_per_week"'/>
							<reset_to after="never">0</reset_to>
						</numeric_input>
					</group_input>
				</stacked_container>
				<text_box font_size="11pt" appearance="transparent" x="454.517" y="88.9534" width="334.185" height="131.6">The default values for average length of stay are derived from Model Hospital (sub-optimal pathway) and expert judgement (early screening pathway). 

The length of stay applied in the model is a weighted average, based on the proportion of referrals to the early screening pathway. Early discharge planning can reduce the additional length of stay due to the delay.</text_box>
			</view>
			<view isee:template_view="template:2" isee:name="Info" background="white" page_width="1066" page_height="600" zoom="125" type="interface">
				<style>
					<isee:stacked_container item_spacing="0" corner_radius="4" selected_item_color="black" selected_item_background="white" item_background="#DDDDDD" transparent_bg="false"/>
				</style>
				<text_box appearance="transparent" x="699.81" y="310.941" width="352.917" height="262.27">&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }
li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }
li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:700; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Credits &amp;amp; Further Information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-weight:700; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;This project was funded by UCL&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Thanks also to:&lt;br /&gt;CPOC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;NHS England&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;GIRFT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Royal College of Anaesthetists&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Royal College of Surgeons&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;leads from Integrated Care Boards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#000000; background-color:#ffffff;&quot;&gt;For further information please contact the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:strategy.unit@nhs.net&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:700; text-decoration: underline; color:#5881c1; background-color:#ffffff;&quot;&gt;Strategy Unit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</text_box>
				<text_box appearance="transparent" x="699.81" y="87.9333" width="323.333" height="189.667">&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }
li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }
li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:700; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Data Sources&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/rtt-waiting-times/&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline; color:#5881c1;&quot;&gt;NHSE RTT Waiting Times&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/populationandmigration&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline; color:#5881c1;&quot;&gt;Office for National Statistics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;National Theatres Productivity dashboard&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Waiting List Minimum Data Set (WLMDS)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;NHSE Secondary Uses Service (SUS) dataset&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Model documentation is available on &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/The-Strategy-Unit/perioperative-care-pathway-model&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline; color:#5881c1;&quot;&gt;Github&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</text_box>
				<text_box appearance="transparent" x="28.9667" y="87.9333" width="507.5" height="488">&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }
li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }
li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:700; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Baseline&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-weight:700; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;The baseline scenario, illustrated in the charts with a dashed blue line, represents the projection of the status quo i.e. referral rates, proportion of O&amp;amp;T referrals requiring hip or knee replacement, OPA and theatre capacity etc. as experienced during the calibration period (2025).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:700; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Assumptions &amp;amp; Simplifications&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-weight:700; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;By the very nature of trying to model a system, a system dynamics model will capture the general behaviours of a system and not the detailed variation within it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;A number of assumptions are built into the model:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;- referral rates are constant throughout the simulation period (unless manually adjusted)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;- probabilities are fixed throughout the simulation period&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;- all RTT without a DTA are waiting for first OPA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;- capacity constraints (OPA and theatre) are approximated by flow rates rather than scheduling&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;- hips &amp;amp; knees theatre allocation is in the same proportion as treated clock stops (28%)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Simplifications include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;- no seasonal variation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;- model excludes diagnostic delays, emergency surgery, staffing constraints&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;- no prioritisation between urgent and routine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;- time allocated for medical optimisation is fixed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;- hospital beds are not capacity-constrained&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</text_box>
			</view>
			<isee:templates>
