			<isee:stories>
				<isee:story uid="120" name="pathway">
					<view isee:template_view="template:7" background="white" page_width="1066" page_height="600" isee:scroll_x="242.401" zoom="125" type="interface">
						<style>
							<isee:stacked_container item_spacing="0" corner_radius="4" selected_item_color="black" selected_item_background="white" item_background="#DDDDDD" transparent_bg="false"/>
						</style>
						<isee:model_view x="0" y="0" width="1066" height="600" isee:locked="true" zoom="1" center_x="565" center_y="316" locked_view="true" transparent="true" use_visible_list="true" show_ltm_table="false">
							<model name="calcs"/>
							<isee:visible_list>
								<entity name="referrals_per_year"/>
								<entity name="referrals_per_day"/>
								<entity name='"o&amp;t_referral_rate_p_10th_pa"'/>
								<entity name="annual_change"/>
								<item uid="calcs.46"/>
								<item uid="calcs.48"/>
								<item uid="calcs.195"/>
								<item uid="calcs.196"/>
								<entity name="population"/>
								<entity name="diversion_ref_rate_per_10th"/>
								<entity name="pop_18_growth_rate_pa"/>
								<item uid="calcs.51"/>
								<entity name="init_pop_18_2025"/>
								<item uid="calcs.49"/>
								<entity name="referral_rate_per_10th"/>
								<item uid="calcs.194"/>
							</isee:visible_list>
							<isee:highlight_list/>
						</isee:model_view>
						<text_box font_size="11pt" x="21.9367" y="107.385" width="343.09" height="427.975">This storyboard walks through the logic underlying the Perioperative Care Pathway modelling.

In its simplest form, there are 2 parallel pathways that share resources (outpatient appointments and theatre capacities).

The early screening pathway is to referred to as &apos;ideal&apos;, the model elements are prefixed with i.

The regular pathway is referred to as sub-optimal, and the model elements are prefixed with s.

The storyboard explains the general flow through the pathways and describes the differences where they occur.

Assumptions are made at various points along the pathway in order to keep the model as simple as possible.</text_box>
						<text_box font_size="11pt" x="456.923" y="383.077" width="370.769" height="138">Demographic changes in population between 2025 and 2035 are accounted for. Using ONS projections, the average annual growth rate for the England adult population has been calculated. 
Using 2025 RTT data, the O&amp;T referral rate per 10 000 has been calculated.

These are combined to give an average daily number of referrals throughout the simulation period, accounting for population growth.</text_box>
						<text_box font_size="11pt" x="843.847" y="322.5" width="211.923" height="144.475">The model includes functionality to reduce the number of referrals to O&amp;T by diverting activity to Primary and/or Community care</text_box>
					</view>
					<view isee:template_view="template:7" background="white" page_width="1066" page_height="600" zoom="125" type="interface">
						<style>
							<isee:stacked_container item_spacing="0" corner_radius="4" selected_item_color="black" selected_item_background="white" item_background="#DDDDDD" transparent_bg="false"/>
						</style>
						<isee:model_view x="0" y="0" width="1066" height="600" isee:locked="true" zoom="0.8" center_x="666.25" center_y="489" locked_view="true" transparent="true" use_visible_list="true" show_ltm_table="false">
							<model name="Top-Level"/>
							<isee:visible_list>
								<item uid="2"/>
								<item uid="176"/>
								<item uid="235"/>
								<item uid="237"/>
								<entity name="i_referrals"/>
								<item uid="236"/>
								<entity name="p_refs_to_hips_knees"/>
								<entity name="s_wait_opa"/>
								<entity name="referrals"/>
								<entity name="s_referrals"/>
								<item uid="1"/>
								<entity name="i_wait_opa"/>
							</isee:visible_list>
							<isee:highlight_list>
								<item uid="237"/>
								<item uid="2"/>
								<item uid="176"/>
								<item uid="235"/>
								<item uid="1"/>
							</isee:highlight_list>
						</isee:model_view>
						<text_box font_size="11pt" x="569.868" y="199.905" width="444.838" height="239.053">A proportion of all O&amp;T referrals are specific to hips and knee issues. In-model calibration  determined this to be 19% in 2025 - this figure remains constant through the simulation period.

At (or around) the time of referral, a proportion of the hip and knee referrals join the early screening pathway. These patients undergo some form of early screening and are risk-stratified by complexity. Modifiable risk factors can start to be addressed at this point. The model assumes:

 - 20% are low complexity
 - 60% medium complexity
 - 20% high complexity

In both pathways, people join a queue while they wait for their first out-patient appointment (OPA).</text_box>
						<text_box font_weight="bold" font_size="16pt" x="18.2308" y="499" width="182.16" height="25.0769">Sub-optimal pathway</text_box>
						<text_box font_weight="bold" font_size="16pt" x="25" y="88.1538" width="152.16" height="49.6923">Ideal pathway (early screening)</text_box>
					</view>
					<view isee:template_view="template:7" background="white" page_width="1066" page_height="600" zoom="125" type="interface">
						<style>
							<isee:stacked_container item_spacing="0" corner_radius="4" selected_item_color="black" selected_item_background="white" item_background="#DDDDDD" transparent_bg="false"/>
						</style>
						<isee:model_view x="0" y="0" width="1066" height="600" isee:locked="true" zoom="0.7" center_x="761.429" center_y="460.571" locked_view="true" transparent="true" use_visible_list="true" show_ltm_table="false">
							<model name="Top-Level"/>
							<isee:visible_list>
								<entity name="i_do_not_proceed_surgery"/>
								<entity name="s_wait_opa"/>
								<item uid="114"/>
								<entity name="i_opa_to_poa"/>
								<entity name="p_fasttrack"/>
								<entity name="i_fasttrack_to_admit"/>
								<entity name="i_wait_poa"/>
								<entity name="s_opa_to_tci"/>
								<entity name="i_wait_opa"/>
								<entity name="s_tci_wait_poa"/>
								<entity name="s_do_not_proceed_surgery"/>
							</isee:visible_list>
							<isee:highlight_list>
								<entity name="surg_demand"/>
								<item uid="114"/>
								<entity name="opt_time"/>
								<item uid="169"/>
								<item uid="170"/>
								<item uid="229"/>
								<entity name="s_wait_opt"/>
								<item uid="36"/>
								<item uid="103"/>
								<entity name="i_preadmit_dropout"/>
								<entity name="s_preadmit_dropout"/>
								<item uid="104"/>
								<item uid="228"/>
								<entity name="s_reopt"/>
							</isee:highlight_list>
						</isee:model_view>
						<text_box font_size="11pt" x="20.3978" y="157.846" width="275.846" height="320.538">The capacity of first out-patient appointments that occur per day is estimated using Little&apos;s Law:

L =λW

where L = number of people queuing (number of open RTT pathways without a DTA)

λ  = appointments per day (to be determined)

W = average time waiting (optimised using in-model calibration as 24.2 weeks)


Allocation of appointments to the ideal and sub-optimal pathways is proportional to the  size of the number of people waiting in each.




</text_box>
						<text_box font_weight="bold" font_size="16pt" x="18.2308" y="499" width="182.16" height="25.0769">Sub-optimal pathway</text_box>
						<text_box font_weight="bold" font_size="16pt" x="25" y="88.1538" width="152.16" height="49.6923">Ideal pathway (early screening)</text_box>
						<text_box font_size="11pt" x="491.936" y="235.538" width="490.233" height="220.538">The outcome of the first OPA is either not to proceed to surgery (~55%), or continue along the pathway with a Decision to Admit (DTA).

The next step is a Pre-Operative Assessment (POA). In the early screening pathway, people assessed as low complexity can have their POA on the same day as OPA, and be fast-tracked to the queue of people waiting for To Come in (TCI) date.

The remaining early screening patients are streamlined at the right time to POA.

In the sub-optimal pathway, all patients with a DTA wait for POA.

</text_box>
					</view>
					<view isee:template_view="template:7" background="white" page_width="1066" page_height="600" zoom="125" type="interface">
						<style>
							<isee:stacked_container item_spacing="0" corner_radius="4" selected_item_color="black" selected_item_background="white" item_background="#DDDDDD" transparent_bg="false"/>
						</style>
						<isee:model_view x="0" y="0" width="1066" height="600" isee:locked="true" zoom="0.65" center_x="1261" center_y="526.538" locked_view="true" transparent="true" use_visible_list="true" show_ltm_table="false">
							<model name="Top-Level"/>
							<isee:visible_list>
								<entity name="i_wait_opa"/>
								<entity name="s_poa_to_ready"/>
								<entity name="s_wait_post_poa"/>
								<entity name="i_do_not_proceed_surgery"/>
								<entity name="s_wait_opa"/>
								<entity name="i_poa_to_opt"/>
								<entity name="s_poa_to_opt"/>
								<entity name="i_opa_to_poa"/>
								<entity name="i_wait_with_tci"/>
								<entity name="s_opa_to_tci"/>
								<entity name="i_poa_to_ready"/>
								<entity name="i_preadmit_dropout"/>
								<entity name="s_preadmit_dropout"/>
								<entity name="i_opt_to_ready"/>
								<entity name="s_reopt"/>
								<entity name="s_opt_to_ready"/>
								<entity name="p_i_re_poa"/>
								<entity name="i_opt_to_poa"/>
								<entity name="s_tci_wait_poa"/>
								<entity name="s_do_not_proceed_surgery"/>
								<item uid="39"/>
								<entity name="i_wait_opt"/>
								<entity name="s_wait_opt"/>
								<entity name="i_fasttrack_to_admit"/>
								<entity name="i_wait_poa"/>
							</isee:visible_list>
							<isee:highlight_list>
								<item uid="106"/>
								<item uid="226"/>
								<entity name="s_cancel_reopt_rate"/>
								<item uid="83"/>
								<item uid="154"/>
								<entity name="same_day_cancellation_need_reopt"/>
								<entity name="surgery_and_recovery"/>
								<item uid="227"/>
							</isee:highlight_list>
						</isee:model_view>
						<text_box font_size="11pt" x="709.628" y="104" width="348.695" height="227.306">In the early screening pathway, medium and high complexity patients are streamlined at the right time to POA. It is assumed that 25% of these patients require medical optimisation, which takes 6 weeks. 20% of these require more time and undergo another cycle of optimisation.

During the POA or optimisation process, patients are given a TCI date and wait for admission.

A small number of patients decline surgery at this stage.</text_box>
						<text_box font_weight="bold" font_size="16pt" x="9.00003" y="382.077" width="182.16" height="25.0769">Sub-optimal pathway</text_box>
						<text_box font_weight="bold" font_size="16pt" x="11.1538" y="254.308" width="152.16" height="49.6923">Ideal pathway (early screening)</text_box>
						<text_box font_size="11pt" x="715.514" y="380" width="336.923" height="172.032">In the sub-optimal pathway, the POA for patients with a DTA is only triggered when they receive a TCI date. 
It is assumed that 40% of these patients require medical optimisation, which takes 6 weeks. In this pathway, there is no option to extend the optimisation period.

A small number of patients decline surgery at this stage.</text_box>
					</view>
					<view isee:template_view="template:8" background="white" page_width="1066" page_height="600" isee:scroll_x="72" zoom="125" type="interface">
						<style>
							<isee:stacked_container item_spacing="0" corner_radius="4" selected_item_color="black" selected_item_background="white" item_background="#DDDDDD" transparent_bg="false"/>
						</style>
						<isee:model_view x="0" y="0" width="1066" height="600" isee:locked="true" zoom="0.65" center_x="1915" center_y="592.538" locked_view="true" transparent="true" use_visible_list="true" show_ltm_table="false">
							<model name="Top-Level"/>
							<isee:visible_list>
								<entity name="delayed_discharge"/>
								<item uid="137"/>
								<item uid="257"/>
								<item uid="256"/>
