				<text_box font_weight="bold" font_size="16pt" uid="56" x="19" y="965" width="264" height="33">VALIDATION/CALIBRATION</text_box>
				<text_box uid="57" x="15.5" y="1012" width="205" height="366">Uses RTT data published monthly
https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/rtt-waiting-times/

Assumptions applied as above to interpolate Hip &amp; Knees.

Dan&apos;s 45% of all DTA for hips &amp; knees - does this include more than just replacements? Hence using SUS %

SUS analysis of IP/daycase procedures:
hips &amp; knee replacements are ~28% of all O&amp;T completed procs

Have SUS completed last episode counts for all elective O&amp;T, and hip/knee replacements.
ALso split by NHS/independent</text_box>
